results.name: a(n) = PrimePi(n) * PrimePi(n^2) - PrimePi(n)^3, where PrimePi = A000720.
comment: All terms are positive except a(1) = a(3) = a(5) = 0 and a(7) = -4, by the PNT with error term for large n and computation for smaller n. In particular, PrimePi(n) * PrimePi(n^2) > PrimePi(n)^3, for n > 7.
For PrimePi(n^3) - PrimePi(n) * PrimePi(n^2), see A291539.
For prime(n)^3 - prime(n) * prime(n^2), see A291542.
